item.title: CVE-2022-3855|2024-08-03T01:20:58.657Z -- unknown -- 404%20to%20start
item.description: The 404 to Start WordPress plugin through 1.6.1 does not sanitise and escape some of its settings, which could allow high privilege users such as admin to perform Stored Cross-Site Scripting attacks even when the unfiltered_html capability is disallowed (for example in multisite setup).
